description:
Hi listeners! We’re taking a break this week, but please enjoy one of our favorite Forever35 episodes from March 2019.


This week, Kate talks about the 12th anniversary of her mom’s death, the ways grief is constantly changing, and her progress with therapy and intuitive eating. Doree details her luxurious bath routine whilst in New York, visiting family, and how she’s staying hydrated while pregnant.

Then they welcome actor and writer Natasha Rothwell (HBO’s Insecure). She breaks down why she recently embraced meditation, astrology, and self-help books, how getting a dog transformed her life, and tips for handling imposter syndrome.

View the original show notes here.
